<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM7.8.10">
<l>paṉṟiyāy mīṉāki yariyāyp pāraip paṭaittukkāt tuṇṭumiḻnta paramaṉ ṟaṉṉai</l>
<l>yaṉṟamarark katipatiyu mayaṉuñ cēyu maṭipaṇiya vaṇiyaḻuntūr niṉṟa kōvai</l>
<l>kaṉṟineṭu vēlvalava ṉāli nāṭaṉ kalikaṉṟi yoliceyta viṉpap pāṭal</l>
<l>oṉṟiṉoṭu nāṉkumō raintum vallā rolikaṭalcū ḻulakāḷu mumpar tāmē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who master these one-plus-four-plus-five sweet songs</l>
<l rend="indent">which Kalikaṉṟi, the one of Āli country, the skilled one</l>
<l rend="indent">hardened to the long spear,</l>
<l>Created with words about the supreme [lord] who, having become a boar,</l>
<l rend="indent">becoming a fish, and becoming a lion,</l>
<l>Having created the earth, protected and consumed [it], spat it out,</l>
<l rend="indent">the king who stands in lovely Aḻuntūr while the first of immortals,</l>
<l>The unborn one, and the ruddy one bow there at his feet,</l>
<l rend="indent">[as] celestials, they will rule the roaring sea-encircled earth.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
